autochooch is currently supported on decunix, irix
and linux. 

To install:

1. Build the executables by using the makefile in autochooch top 
directory to build Benny_auto, Chooch_auto
and wasel executables. The object files and executables
are generated in autochooch/decunix, autochooch/irix
or autochooch/linux depending on the platform
it is built on. Type,

> cd autochooch
> gmake

2. Install the data files, executables and shell scripts
in the distribution location such as /user/local/autochooch.

Edit autochooch/makefile

Set the INSTALL dir variable, for example
INSTALL_DIR=/user/local/autochooch

> gmake install

The data files from autochooch/data will be copied to 
/user/local/autochooch/data. The executables and scripts
are copied to /user/local/autochooch/bin.

3. Set the env variables so that the the executables
and scripts can be found in the executable paths.
Also set CHOOCHDAT env variable so that the scripts
know where to find the necessary input data files.

> setenv PATH /user/local/autochooch/bin:$PATH
> setenv CHOOCHDAT /user/local/autochooch/data



